{
    "title": "Victoria's Computer Addiction",
    "content": "Lately, I've been feeling like my very being has fallen prey to computer addiction. It started a few years back, when my husband's colleagues began inviting him over for cocktails and pizza parties on weekends. At first, I brushed it off as idle curiosity or an unwanted social obligation; but something inside me began to change. I started sneaking away during those evenings to do some real work at my computer. Days turned into weeks, and before I knew it, I was spending over a third of my weekly work hours staring at the screen."
