temp_0.7_output:
{
  "title": "Computers are a Curse for My Family",
  "content": "As a mother of three, I am not one to speak much, but today I would like to share with you my deep-seated feelings about computers. It started the moment I laid eyes on my first computer. It was an old, clunky machine that sat in my living room like a monstrosity. At the time, I had no idea what I was getting myself into. What started as a small, harmless object turned out to be something far more sinister: a tool of destruction. For me, computers are nothing but a curse. As a mother, watching my children stare at their screens for hours on end is the most depressing thing I have ever seen. The sight of my youngest daughter sitting in front of her computer, lost in her video game world while my oldest son sits across from me typing away at work, is enough to make any mother's heart sink. As a parent, it is hard to watch your children become addicted to technology. It's like watching them grow weed. The screens are there, but they aren't there for the right reasons."

 																			,"word_count":100, "style_elements":["list", "heading", "paragraph"] }

